quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  44,17,"Indeed, We tested the people of Pharaoh before them, when a noble messenger came to them"
  44,18,"[saying], “Hand over to me the slaves of Allah. I am indeed a trustworthy messenger to you"
  44,19,and do not be arrogant towards Allah. I have certainly come to you with a clear proof
  44,20,"And I certainly seek refuge with my Lord and your Lord, lest you stone me to death"
  44,21,"If you do not believe me, then leave me alone.”"
  44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord, “These are a wicked people”"
  44,23,"[Allah said], “Leave along with My slaves by night; you will surely be pursued"
  44,24,And leave the sea parted; for they are surely an army destined to drown.”
  44,25,"[Imagine] how many gardens and springs they left behind"
  44,26,and crops and splendid mansions
  44,27,and luxuries they used to rejoice therein
  44,28,So it was; and We made another people inherit all that
  44,29,"Neither the heaven nor earth wept for them, nor were they given any respite"
  44,30,Thus did We save the Children of Israel from the humiliating punishment
  44,31,from Pharaoh. He was indeed arrogant who transgressed all bounds
  44,32,We chose them with knowledge above all others
  44,33,And We gave them signs in which there was a clear test
  44,34,"Indeed, these [Makkans] say"
  44,35,"“There is nothing after our first death, and we will not be resurrected"
  44,36,then bring back our forefathers if you are truthful.”
  44,37,"Are they better [in power] or the people of Tubba‘ and those who were before them? We destroyed them, for they were truly wicked"
  44,38,We have not created the heavens and earth and all that is between them for amusement
  44,39,"We have not created them except for a true purpose, but most of them do not know"
  44,40,"Indeed, the Day of Judgment is the time appointed for them all"
  44,41,"the Day when no friend will avail another in the least, nor will they be helped"
  44,42,"except those to whom Allah shows mercy. He is indeed the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful"
  44,43,"Indeed, the tree of Zaqqūm"
  44,44,will be the food of the sinful
  44,45,like molten metal that will boil in their bellies
  44,46,like the boiling of scalding water
  44,47,"[It will be said], “Seize him and drag him into the midst of the Blazing Fire"
  44,48,Then pour over his head the torment of scalding water.”
  44,49,“Taste this. You are surely the mighty and honorable
  44,50,"This is what you [all] used to doubt.”"
  44,51,"Indeed, the righteous will be in a safe place"
  44,52,in gardens and springs
  44,53,"wearing fine silk and heavy brocade, facing one another"
  44,54,"So it will be, and We will marry them to maidens with gorgeous eyes"
  44,55,"They will call therein for every kind of fruit, safe and secure"
  44,56,"They will not taste death therein except the first death, and He will protect them from the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  44,57,as a grace from your Lord. That is the supreme triumph
  44,58,"We have made this [Qur’an] easy in your own language, so that they may take heed"
  44,59,Then wait; they too are waiting
  45,1,Hā Mīm
  45,2,"The revelation of this Book is from Allah, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  45,3,"Indeed, there are signs in the heavens and earth for the believers"
  45,4,"and in your creation and the living creatures that He spreads out, there are signs for people who are certain in faith"
  45,5,"And in the alternation of the night and day, the provision that Allah sends down from the sky, reviving thereby the earth after its death, and directing of the winds, there are signs for people of understanding"
  45,6,These are the signs of Allah that We recite to you in truth. What message will they believe in after Allah and His signs
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"who hears the verses of Allah being recited to him, yet he persists in his arrogance, as if he did not hear them. So give him tidings of a painful punishment"
  45,9,"When he comes to know anything of Our verses, he takes them in ridicule. For them there will be a humiliating punishment"
  45,10,"Behind them is Hell; neither their gains nor those whom they took besides Allah as protectors will avail them anything, and for them there will be a great punishment"
  45,11,"This [Qur’an] is guidance, and for those who disbelieve in the verses of their Lord there will be scourge of painful torment"